      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(anthropic): handle max_turns stop reason and surface retry-limit details to users",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: When `max_turns` API guardrail fires, the Anthropic provider throws `Unhandled stop reason: max_turns` instead of mapping it to a known stop reason. Additionally, when the embedded runner exhausts retry limits (including max-turn loops), users see only a generic error message without the actionable failure context (attempt count, limit value, breaker reason).\n- Solution: Add `max_turns` to `mapStopReason` in both Anthropic mappers, and surface the detailed retry-limit exhaustion reason in the user-visible error payload.\n- What changed: 3 source files (2 Anthropic mappers + retry-limit handler) and 1 new regression test file.\n- What did NOT change: No changes to the retry loop, failover policy, idle-timeout breaker logic, or any other provider/transport path.\n\nFixes #78145\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** `max_turns` stop reason was unhandled, and retry-limit exhaustion produced a generic user-facing message instead of including the detailed failure context.\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS 26.5 (arm64), Node v24.15.0, OpenClaw main @ b2c2936\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  ```bash\n  # Start the OpenClaw gateway to verify the Anthropic mapper code (including\n  # the new max_turns case) loads and the gateway reaches \"ready\" state:\n  OPENCLAW_SKIP_CHANNELS=1 node scripts/run-node.mjs --dev gateway\n\n  # Run the full Anthropic transport-stream test suite:\n  npx vitest run src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts\n\n  # Run the full Anthropic provider test suite:\n  npx vitest run src/llm/providers/anthropic.test.ts\n\n  # Run the new retry-limit regression tests:\n  npx vitest run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/retry-limit.test.ts\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  Gateway startup — builds, loads providers/plugins, reaches \"ready\" without errors:\n  ```\n  [openclaw] Building TypeScript (dist is stale: config_newer - config newer than build stamp).\n  [openclaw] Building bundled plugin assets.\n  runtime-postbuild: plugin SDK root alias completed in 1ms\n  runtime-postbuild: bundled plugin metadata completed in 96ms\n  runtime-postbuild: official channel catalog completed in 2ms\n  runtime-postbuild: bundled plugin runtime overlay completed in 221ms\n  runtime-postbuild: static extension assets completed in 83ms\n  runtime-postbuild: stable root runtime imports completed in 150ms\n  runtime-postbuild: stable root runtime aliases completed in 26ms\n  runtime-postbuild: legacy root runtime compat aliases completed in 4ms\n  runtime-postbuild: legacy CLI exit compat chunks completed in 0ms\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.358+08:00 Dev config ready: ~/.openclaw-dev/openclaw.json\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.364+08:00 Dev workspace ready: ~/.openclaw/workspace-dev\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.370+08:00 [gateway] loading configuration…\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.399+08:00 [gateway] resolving authentication…\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.408+08:00 [gateway] starting...\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.586+08:00 [gateway] starting HTTP server...\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.606+08:00 [health-monitor] started (interval: 300s, startup-grace: 60s, channel-connect-grace: 120s)\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.769+08:00 [gateway] agent model: openai/gpt-5.5 (thinking=medium, fast=off)\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.770+08:00 [gateway] http server listening (9 plugins: acpx, bonjour, browser, canvas, device-pair, file-transfer, memory-core, phone-control, talk-voice; 0.4s)\n  2026-06-17T20:42:51.771+08:00 [gateway] ready\n  ```\n\n  Anthropic transport-stream tests — 148 passing, including all existing stop-reason handling:\n  ```\n  Test Files  2 passed (2)\n       Tests  148 passed (148)\n  ```\n\n  Anthropic provider tests — 35 passing:\n  ```\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n       Tests  35 passed (35)\n  ```\n\n  Retry-limit regression tests — 4 passing:\n  ```\n   ✓ handleRetryLimitExhaustion (4)\n     ✓ includes the detailed reason message in the user-visible payload text\n     ✓ preserves the detailed message in meta.error\n     ✓ throws FailoverError when decision action is fallback_model\n     ✓ includes the detailed message for idle-timeout breaker exhaustion\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** Gateway starts cleanly with the patched Anthropic mapper code — no `Unhandled stop reason` crash. All 183 existing Anthropic-related tests pass unchanged, confirming the new `max_turns` case doesn't affect existing stop-reason routing. The retry-limit handler now surfaces the detailed failure context (attempt count, max limit, breaker reason) in the user-visible payload instead of a generic message.\n- **What was not tested:** End-to-end trigger of the Anthropic `max_turns` stop reason requires exhausting the API turn budget, which is not feasible to force on demand. The fix is verified by: (1) the gateway loads and runs the patched mapper code without errors, (2) the `mapStopReason` switch statement now explicitly handles `max_turns` alongside the existing `pause_turn` case with the same return value, (3) all 183 existing Anthropic stop-reason tests continue to pass.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- Coverage level: Unit test\n- Target test file: `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/retry-limit.test.ts`\n- Scenario locked in: Detailed reason message included in user-visible error text; message preserved in meta.error; FailoverError thrown for fallback_model decisions; idle-timeout breaker message surfaced.\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: The test exercises `handleRetryLimitExhaustion` directly with realistic params matching both caller paths (max loop iterations and idle-timeout circuit breaker).\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- Root cause: The Anthropic API `max_turns` stop reason was introduced after the two `mapStopReason` mappers were written, so it fell through to the `default` branch throwing `Unhandled stop reason`. Separately, `handleRetryLimitExhaustion` received a detailed `message` param from callers but only stored it in `meta.error`, while the user-visible payload text was a hardcoded generic string.\n- Missing detection / guardrail: No exhaustive switch check or `satisfies` constraint on the stop reason mapping to catch new API values at compile time.",
